canonical:
  title: 賜金富佾守太尉判秘書省事
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 敎卿任天下之重爲學者之師而退託於微痾以祈解其繁務爰擇秩崇而事簡就易淸資其惟心靜則氣平行膺異渥
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賜金富佾守太尉判秘書省事
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 敎。卿任天下之重。爲學者之師。而退託於微痾。以祈解其繁務。爰擇秩崇而事簡。就易淸資。其惟心靜則氣平。行膺異渥。
korean:
  title: 사 김부일 수태위 판비서성사
  author: 최유청
  language: kor
  text: 교하노라. 경은 천하의 무거운 책임을 지고 있고, 학자의 스승자리에 앉아 있다. 그런데 하찮은 병을 칭탁하고 번잡한 정무에서 벗어나기를 원하였다. 이에 등급을 높이고 일이 간단한 자리를 택하여, 청직(淸職)으로 바꾼다. 마음이 고요하면 기운이 화평해지는 것이니, 가서 특별한 은혜를 받으라.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0280_010_0060&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Edict Appointing Kim Bu-il as Guardian General and Judge of the Secret Secretariat
  author: Choi Yu-cheong
  language: eng
  text: 'Thus it is decreed: You bear the weight of the realm upon your shoulders and stand as a teacher to all scholars. Yet claiming ailment, you seek to lay down the burdens of office. Therefore, we raise your rank and assign you to a post of lighter duties, granting you a position of serene authority. Know that when the heart is still, the spirit finds harmony. Go forth and receive this extraordinary grace.'
  footnotes:
    - The 'edict of appointment' (敎) was an official form of imperial or high-level bureaucratic communication in Classical Chinese governance
    - The reference to 'heart still, spirit harmonious' (心靜則氣平) reflects Neo-Confucian philosophical principles about inner cultivation and outer governance
